<exercise checkit-seed="0005" checkit-slug="AI2" checkit-title="Arc Length">
    <statement>
        <p>
            Consider the curve <m>y=-3 \, x^{3}</m> defined on <m>[0, 1]</m>.
            <ol>
                <li>
                    Estimate the arclength of this curve with <m>5</m> line segments with <m>\Delta x = 0.2</m>.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Find an integral that computes the arclength of this curve.
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
        
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <me>
               \begin{array}{|c|c|c|c|c|}
              \hline
              x_i
              &amp;
              x_{i+1}
              &amp;
              f(x_{i})
              &amp;
              f(x_{i+1})
              &amp;
              \text{Length of segment}          
              \\
              \hline
               0
              &amp; 
               0.2
              &amp;
               0.0
              &amp; 
               -0.024
              &amp;
               0.2014         
                  \\
               0.2
              &amp; 
               0.4
              &amp;
               -0.024
              &amp; 
               -0.192
              &amp;
               0.2612         
                  \\
               0.4
              &amp; 
               0.6000000000000001
              &amp;
               -0.192
              &amp; 
               -0.648
              &amp;
               0.4979         
                  \\
               0.6
              &amp; 
               0.8
              &amp;
               -0.648
              &amp; 
               -1.536
              &amp;
               0.9102         
                  \\
               0.8
              &amp; 
               1.0
              &amp;
               -1.536
              &amp; 
               -3.0
              &amp;
               1.4776         
                  \\
              
              \hline
              \end{array}
          </me>
              The estimated length of this curve is 3.3483.      
                </li>
                <li>
                    The arclength is computed via <me>\int_{ 0 }^{ 1 }\sqrt{1+ \left(-9 \, x^{2}\right)^2}dx.</me> 
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
